1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,530
Two.

2
00:00:01,040 --> 00:00:02,770
What causes quarrels?

3
00:00:03,760 --> 00:00:07,409
Ever stop to ask yourself just what causes quarrels?

4
00:00:07,599 --> 00:00:14,050
At least ninety-nine percent of the time, quarrels start over petty, unimportant matters like this.

5
00:00:14,479 --> 00:00:17,810
John comes home a little tired, a little on edge.

6
00:00:17,999 --> 00:00:23,169
Dinner doesn't exactly please him, so he turns up his nose and complains.

7
00:00:23,599 --> 00:00:28,689
Joan's day wasn't perfect either, so she rallies to her own defense with,

8
00:00:28,800 --> 00:00:31,490
well, what do you expect on my food budget?

9
00:00:31,599 --> 00:00:36,289
Or, maybe I could cook better if I had a new stove like everybody else.

10
00:00:36,639 --> 00:00:42,689
This insults John's pride, so he attacks with, now Joan, it's not lack of money,

11
00:00:42,719 --> 00:00:45,729
it's simply that you don't know how to manage.

12
00:00:46,159 --> 00:00:47,890
And away they go.

13
00:00:48,159 --> 00:00:54,129
Before a truce is finally declared, all sorts of accusations are made by each party.

14
00:00:54,320 --> 00:01:01,890
In-laws, sex, money, premarital and postmarital promises, and other issues will be introduced.

15
00:01:02,159 --> 00:01:05,410
Both parties leave the battle nervous, tense.

16
00:01:05,599 --> 00:01:11,890
Nothing has been settled, and both parties have new ammunition to make the next quarrel more vicious.

17
00:01:12,239 --> 00:01:15,649
Little things, petty thinking, causes arguments.

18
00:01:15,760 --> 00:01:19,649
So, to eliminate quarrels, eliminate petty thinking.

19
00:01:20,079 --> 00:01:22,050
Here's a technique that works.

20
00:01:22,399 --> 00:01:32,370
Before complaining or accusing or reprimanding someone or launching a counterattack in self-defense, ask yourself, is it really important?

21
00:01:32,559 --> 00:01:36,370
In most cases, it isn't, and you avoid conflict.

22
00:01:36,879 --> 00:01:46,850
Ask yourself, is it really important if he or she is messy with cigarettes or forgets to put the cap on the toothpaste or is late coming home?

23
00:01:47,039 --> 00:01:53,970
Is it really important if he or she squandered a little money or invited some people in I don't like?

24
00:01:54,559 --> 00:02:00,129
When you feel like taking negative action, ask yourself, is it really important?

25
00:02:00,479 --> 00:02:05,010
That question works magic in building a finer home situation.

26
00:02:05,119 --> 00:02:07,010
It works at the office, too.

27
00:02:07,280 --> 00:02:11,570
It works in home-going traffic when another driver cuts in ahead of you.

28
00:02:11,599 --> 00:02:16,209
It works in any situation in life that is apt to produce quarrels.

29
00:02:16,209 --> 00:02:17,970
3.

